            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-01-05T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-05-31T23:30:00-05:00" n="1061" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d1061">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>The <hi rend="italic">Ad Hoc</hi> Political Committee made its report to the
                    General Assembly on December 7; for its text, see United Nations, <hi
                        rend="italic">Official Records of the Fourth Session of the General
                        Assembly, Plenary Meetings of the General Assembly, Annex to the Summary
                        Records of Meetings, 1949</hi> (hereinafter identified as <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">4th sess., Plenary,
                    Annex</hi>), page 35. The report included two draft resolutions adopted by the
                    Committee for consideration by the General Assembly. One concerned the questions
                    of an international regime for the Jerusalem area and of the protection of the
                    Holy Places, the Committee adopting the recommendations of Subcommittee 1 by a
                    vote of 35 to 13, with 11 abstentions. <pb facs="1544" n="1528" xml:id="pg_1528"
                    /> The second draft resolution dealt with the question of assistance to the
                    Palestine refugees, which the Committee adopted by 48 votes to none, with 6
                    abstentions. For the texts of the two draft resolutions, see <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">4th Sess., Plenary,
                    Annex</hi>, pages 38 and 39. For the proceedings of the Committee from December
                    5 to 7, see <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>, <hi rend="italic">4th sess., Ad
                        Hoc Political Committee</hi>, pages 339–368.</p>
            </div>
